      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[AI] fix(gateway): reuse active dashboard session key on reconnect",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nControl UI reconnect no longer orphans the active dashboard session by generating a new `dashboard:<UUID>` key.\r\n- Problem: `sessions.create` always generates a random `agent:<agentId>:dashboard:<UUID>` key when called without a `requestedKey`. On every Control UI reconnect, this creates a new dashboard session and orphans the previous one, losing conversation context.\r\n- Solution: When `requestedKey` is absent, scan the agent session store for an existing active (no `endedAt`) dashboard session key first. If found, return its key and entry directly instead of creating a new session.\r\n- What changed: `src/gateway/server-methods/sessions.ts` (+17 lines helper + 18 lines call site), `src/gateway/server.sessions.create.test.ts` (+64 lines, 3 new tests)\r\n- What did NOT change: Explicit \"New Session\" flow (`emitCommandHooks` + `parentSessionKey` path); explicit key create; session resolve/patch/reset behavior; Control UI code\r\n\r\n## Change Type (select all)\r\n\r\n- [x] Bug fix\r\n- [ ] Feature\r\n- [ ] Refactor required for the fix\r\n- [ ] Docs\r\n- [ ] Security hardening\r\n- [ ] Chore/infra\r\n\r\n## Scope (select all)\r\n\r\n- [x] Gateway / orchestration\r\n- [ ] Skills / tool execution\r\n- [ ] Auth / tokens\r\n- [ ] Memory / storage\r\n- [ ] Integrations\r\n- [ ] API / contracts\r\n- [ ] UI / DX\r\n- [ ] CI/CD / infra\r\n\r\n## Linked Issue/PR\r\n\r\n- Related to #95042\r\n- Related to #91664, #89760, #74640, #73546 (session persistence issues part of same regression cascade)\r\n- [x] This PR fixes a bug or regression\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n\r\n`src/gateway/server-methods/sessions.ts:1468` (`buildDashboardSessionKey`) generates a new random UUID every time the Control UI calls `sessions.create` without an explicit key — which happens on every browser refresh, tab reopen, or gateway reconnect. The resulting orphaned `dashboard:<UUID>` entries accumulate and the user loses access to ongoing conversation context. The 2026.6.x session-metadata migration and #92856 session workspace rail made this worse by changing client-side session key management, but the root mechanism (unconditional UUID generation) is an independent bug.\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\n**Behavior addressed**: `sessions.create` without `requestedKey` generates a new `dashboard:<UUID>` on every call, orphaning existing active dashboard sessions on Control UI reconnect.\r\n\r\n**Real environment tested**: OpenClaw dev worktree, Node v24.13.1, Linux x86_64, `fix/dashboard-session-reconnect-95042` branch.\r\n\r\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\r\n\r\n1. `pnpm test src/gateway/server.sessions.create.test.ts` — 32 tests (29 existing + 3 new), all passing\r\n2. New test `sessions.create without key reuses existing active dashboard session` proves the fix\r\n\r\n**Evidence after fix**:\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ pnpm test src/gateway/server.sessions.create.test.ts -t \"without key\"\r\n\r\n ✓ |gateway-server| ../../src/gateway/server.sessions.create.test.ts (16 tests) 9124ms\r\n ✓ |gateway-methods| ../../src/gateway/server.sessions.create.test.ts (16 tests) 7247ms\r\n\r\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\r\n      Tests  32 passed (32)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Behavior matrix**:\r\n\r\n| Input state | Before fix | After fix |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n| No `requestedKey`, no existing dashboard session | New `dashboard:<UUID>` created | New `dashboard:<UUID>` created (unchanged) |\r\n| No `requestedKey`, active dashboard session exists | New `dashboard:<UUID>` created, old orphaned | Existing active dashboard session reused |\r\n| No `requestedKey`, ended dashboard session exists | New `dashboard:<UUID>` created | New `dashboard:<UUID>` created (unchanged) |\r\n| Explicit `requestedKey` (\"main\", `agent:<id>:main`, etc.) | Uses requested key (unchanged) | Uses requested key (unchanged) |\r\n| \"New Session\" with `parentSessionKey` + `emitCommandHooks` | Session reset on parent (unchanged) | Session reset on parent (unchanged) |\r\n\r\n**Observed result after fix**:\r\n\r\n1. **No existing dashboard session** → creates new `dashboard:<UUID>` — no change in behavior\r\n2. **Active dashboard session exists** → returns existing key + entry without creating new session or transcript\r\n3. **Ended dashboard session exists** → creates new `dashboard:<UUID>` — no change in behavior\r\n4. All existing 29 tests continue to pass\r\n\r\n**What was not tested**: Live Control UI browser flow (requires a full gateway + browser session). The fix is verified at the RPC protocol level via gateway test harness.\r\n\r\n## Root Cause (if applicable)\r\n\r\n`buildDashboardSessionKey()` at `src/gateway/server-methods/sessions.ts:342` unconditionally generates `agent:<agentId>:dashboard:${randomUUID()}`. When `sessions.create` is called without a `requestedKey` (Control UI reconnect path), the only choice is \"create new\" — there is no code path to discover and reuse an existing active dashboard session.\r\n\r\n## Regression Test Plan\r\n\r\n3 new tests in `src/gateway/server.sessions.create.test.ts`:\r\n1. No key + existing active dashboard → reuses existing key\r\n2. No key + no dashboard sessions → creates new key\r\n3. No key + ended dashboard session only → creates new key (does not reuse ended)\r\nAll 32 tests pass (29 existing + 3 new).\r\n\r\n## User-visible / Behavior Changes\r\n\r\nPositive: Control UI browser refresh or reconnect no longer loses the active dashboard session — conversation context is preserved. No change for explicit \"New Session\" actions.\r\n\r\n## Security Impact\r\n\r\n- [x] New permissions/capabilities? No\r\n- [x] Secrets/tokens handling changed? No\r\n- [x] New/changed network calls? No\r\n- [x] Command/tool execution surface changed? No\r\n- [x] Data access scope changed? No\r\n\r\n## Human Verification\r\n\r\n- Verified scenarios: Active dashboard session reused on create-without-key; ended dashboard session not reused; empty store creates new\r\n- Edge cases checked: `requestedKey` not provided; `parentSessionKey` not provided; store has non-dashboard keys too; store has multiple dashboard entries (picks latest)\r\n- What you did NOT verify: Live Control UI browser reconnect flow\r\n\r\n## Compatibility / Migration\r\n\r\n- [x] Backward compatible? Yes\r\n- [x] Config/env changes? No\r\n- [x] Migration needed? No\r\n\r\n## Best-fix Verdict\r\n\r\n- **Best fix**: Yes. The fix operates at the same boundary where the bug manifests (the `sessions.create` key selection). Fixing at the UI level would also work, but the gateway-side fix is more robust — it protects all clients including TUI, CLI, and programmatic callers.\r\n- **Refactor needed**: No. The change is bounded (1 helper function + 1 early-return guard in one file).\r\n- **Alternative considered**: Fixing at the Control UI client (persist dashboard key in `localStorage`). Rejected because it only fixes web clients and still allows programmatic callers to trigger the same orphan problem.\r\n\r\n## AI Assistance\r\n\r\n- **AI-assisted**: Yes\r\n- **Human confirmed understanding of code changes**: Yes\r\n- **AI model**: deepseek-v4-flash\r\n- **AI prompts / session excerpts**: Root cause analysis of `buildDashboardSessionKey` provenance in `sessions.create` handler. Design reviewed with user before implementation.\r\n\r\n## Risks and Mitigations\r\n\r\n**Highest risk area**: A caller that intentionally wants a fresh dashboard session without an explicit key would now get the existing one instead. However, the explicit \"New Session\" flow (Control UI `/new` command) already uses the `parentSessionKey` + `emitCommandHooks` path, which is unaffected.\r\n**Mitigation**: The `findActiveDashboardSessionKey` helper only returns sessions without `endedAt`, so completed sessions are never reused. The logged-in behavior only differs for reconnect scenarios, not intentional new-session actions.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nRelated to #95042\r\n",
